Bit Balancer is a lightweight digital logic tool designed to handle and process binary operations efficiently. It provides a reliable way to manage bit-level computations, making it useful for students, hobbyists, and engineers working with digital electronics, Verilog designs, or low-level programming tasks.

Features:
Efficient bit manipulation and balancing

Handles binary inputs and produces accurate results

Lightweight and easy to integrate into larger projects

Clear modular design for better understanding and modifications

Tools Used: [e.g., Verilog, C, Python, etc.]

Environment: Works on any modern system

Use Cases:
Educational projects to understand binary operations

Digital logic simulations

Experimenting with bitwise operations in custom designs

Integration into embedded systems or ALU (Arithmetic Logic Unit) design
